that are in this area.

00:41:16.556 --> 00:41:18.766 A:middle
Finally, in the public database,

00:41:19.076 --> 00:41:22.336 A:middle
by default every record
can be read by every user,

00:41:23.346 --> 00:41:25.426 A:middle
and it can be created
by any user.

00:41:25.726 --> 00:41:29.016 A:middle
Once you create a record, that
record can only be updated

00:41:29.016 --> 00:41:31.096 A:middle
or deleted by the
user that created it.

00:41:32.106 --> 00:41:34.296 A:middle
But we understand that that
doesn't provide all the

00:41:34.296 --> 00:41:36.746 A:middle
functionality that you might
need to make an application

00:41:36.746 --> 00:41:37.766 A:middle
in the public database.

00:41:38.356 --> 00:41:41.186 A:middle
So, what we've given you
are what we call roles.

00:41:41.186 --> 00:41:44.106 A:middle
These roles let you
choose sets of users

00:41:44.106 --> 00:41:46.606 A:middle
that have different
permissions for record types

00:41:46.606 --> 00:41:47.696 A:middle
in the public database.

00:41:48.566 --> 00:41:52.156 A:middle
So, one example of that might
be that I want to restrict it

00:41:52.156 --> 00:41:55.056 A:middle
so that only I can create
parties in the public database.

00:41:55.716 --> 00:41:57.106 A:middle
So, what I'm going
to do in order to do

00:41:57.106 --> 00:41:58.556 A:middle
that is create a new role.

